# **Ex 8:** Correlations

## -8.3

```{r}
#| echo: false
vars <- df %>% select(attend, termGPA, priGPA, ACT, final, atndrte, hwrte)
ggpairs(vars)
```

Insights: The pair of variables that have highest positive correlation are termGPA and priGPA. The correlation statistic is 0.653. Yes it makes sense because it is logical that students who have maintained a high GPA previously, are likely to continue to perform well in the current term. The Nest highest correlation is between variables attend and atndrte. The more effective way to improve GPA's would be atndrte and termGPA, as attendance rate has a stronger positive correlation with term GPA.

